<h1>The Web Service</h1>
The <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/App_Code/Service.vb">Web service</a> provides data to and receives data from the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/">PDA application</a>.
Data from the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/">PDA</a> is written into loading tables in SQL. The connection to the SQL database is specified in the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/">web.config file</a>. When the web service receives data it notifies the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/ProcSVC">Priority Procedure Service</a> to run the loading. <br><br>
The service runs under IIS, on the customers network. This does not have to be the Priority server, but MUST be a machine with priority installed. The customer must make appropriate changes to their firewall to allow connection from the outside to the service.<br><br>
The web service provides a <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/signature.aspx">page</a> that outputs signature data received from the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/">PDA</a> as an image, so that it can be included in Priority Reports.<br><br>
Signature data is stored as an array of vectors that make up the signature image (eg <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/signatures/OCUNVLOU.SIG">signtaure.sig</a>). 
These files are stored by the service in the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/signatures/">signatures</a> folder.<br><br>
When an error occurs in the processing of data received from the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/PDAOnBoardData/">PDA</a> the data is stored in the <a href="http://ntsa.redmartian.org/projects.cgi?codepage=/v13PDA/priwebsvc/badmail/">badmail</a> folder and an event log is generated.<br><br>